                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
                "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Spellgun",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Treasure Vault",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Treasure Vault pg. 221",
                            "alt": "Treasure Vault pg. 221",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 191
                        },
                        "page": 221,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 191
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "890556826496c12df122838e112a1723",
                "text": "The spellgun trait appears on items that can generate a magical effect that flies out like a bullet. You can make either a spell attack roll with a spellgun or a ranged attack roll using your proficiency with simple firearms. Spellguns have a range increment, which applies regardless of which type of attack roll you make. Though you can use your modifier for simple firearms, a spellgun isn't actually a firearm. You don't get the damage of a firearm Strike, nor other benefits like critical specialization. Similarly, you can't load or reload a spellgun, affix talismans to one, make a spellgun Strike as part of an action that lets you make a firearm Strike, and so on.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "firearms",
                        "alt": "firearms",
                        "game-obj": "WeaponGroups",
                        "aonid": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "critical specialization",
                        "alt": "critical specialization",
                        "game-obj": "Rules",
                        "aonid": 235
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "talismans",
                        "alt": "talismans",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 155
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Void",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 118,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 463",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 463",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
