            "type": "stat_block_section",
            "subtype": "save_results",
            "critical_success": "The target takes 4d6 void damage and is \ndrained 2\n and \ndoomed 1\n. If it had fewer than half its maximum Hit Points after taking the void damage, it's drained 3 instead. If the Hit Point loss from being drained drops the creature to 0 Hit Points, it dies.",
            "success": "As critical success, but for the drained condition, the target is drained 1, or drained 2 if it had fewer than half its maximum HP.",
